By Ernest Nzor, Abuja Prominent youth leader in Delta State and logistics mogul, Mr Ojitevwobo Agberhiere, has said that he is not contesting for Okpe Sapele and Uvwie Federal Constituency seat in 2023. According to Agberhiere, in a press statement signed by himself and made available to LEADERSHIP today, he was reacting to a news published by some online blogs, that he was vying for the Federal Constituency Seat. He said that his main focus is to invest in human capital development, and help as many youths as possible. “My principal focus is to invest in human capital development, and help as many youths as possible. “The general public should also discard rumours linking me to the deputy governorship slot, to pair with one of the strong contenders for the governorship position in 2023. It is untrue, lacking in substance, and remains in the imagination of the writers.” He called on the youths of Delta State, to be proactive, and stated that, if he has any political interest, it will be made known publicly by him, and not through rumors. 